<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"] - Lab 4</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/StyleSheet.css" />
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Header 区域：你的名字 + 欢迎语 -->
    <header style="background-color: #f0f0f0; padding: 15px;">
        <h1>Welcome to Lab 4</h1>
        <p>Created by Huijun Bu</p>
        <nav>
            @Html.ActionLink("Home", "Index", "Home") |
            @Html.ActionLink("Show the song!", "SongForm", "Home") |
            @Html.ActionLink("Students", "CreateStudent", "Home")
        </nav>
    </header>

    <!-- 主体内容区域 -->
    <main role="main" style="padding: 20px;">
        @RenderBody()
    </main>

    <!-- Footer 区域：解释 Layout 和 CSS 设置 -->
    <footer style="margin-top: 40px; padding: 20px; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; background-color: #fafafa;">
        <h3>Layout & CSS Setup Explanation</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>What Layout does:</strong> The layout file (_Layout.cshtml) defines a common structure for all views. It includes shared elements such as the header, footer, and navigation bar, ensuring consistency across pages.</li>
            <li>
                <strong>Why we place files in those directories:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>_Layout.cshtml</code> is stored in <code>Views/Shared</code> because it is reused by multiple views and should be accessible across controllers.</li>
                    <li><code>StyleSheet.css</code> is stored in <code>wwwroot/css</code> because <code>wwwroot</code> is the default public folder for static assets like stylesheets, JavaScript, and images in ASP.NET Core projects.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Note:</strong> As required, we did not include the actual contents of the CSS file here.</li>
        </ul>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
